        <div1 type="summary">
            <p><add hand="#barker">Introducing Dixon, and asking for information.</add></p>
        </div1>
        <div1 type="body">
            

<p><placeName>Jackson </placeName><date when="1821-12-22">22nd December 1821</date></p>
<p><persName>S. F. Austin Esqr</persName></p>

<p>Permit me to introduce to your particular acquaintance <persName>Capt
Dixon</persName> the <persName>bearer </persName>of this, as he intends visiting the<persName> province of
Texas</persName>, for the purpose of being a useful citizen in the bounds of<pb n="453"/>
your <placeName>settlement</placeName>&#8212;He has lately been employed in surveying public
Lands in the <placeName>State of Missouri</placeName> and <placeName>Illinois</placeName>, and whose capability,
steadiness and integraty, has met the cordial approbation of his
<persName>employers </persName>as well as general <persName>Government</persName>&#8212;Any friendship that you
may think proper to extend toward him, in that line, or any other
that may be beneficial to him, will be acknowledged by your friend
and humble servt</p>

<p><persName>Erasmus Ellis  </persName>  [Rubric]</p>

<p>P. S.   I wrote to you last month when I was at my <persName>Brother</persName>s on
the <placeName>coast</placeName>, and I hope you will spare time enough to give me general
information of that country; and particularly what kind of 
<persName>Mechanics </persName>are most in demand there at present&#8212;</p>
<p>With respect I am yours etc</p>

<p><persName>E Ellis </persName>   [Rubric]</p>

        </div1>
